## 2. Arrays

An **array** in Go has a fixed length as part of its type. The language spec lists arrays among the composite literal types, but for everyday work you will usually prefer slices. ([Go][3])

```go
package main

import "fmt"

func main() {
    colors := [3]string{"red", "blue", "green"}
    fmt.Println(colors)
}
```

Access works the same way:

```go
fmt.Println(colors[0])
fmt.Println(colors[2])
```

### Slice vs array

Slice:

```go
foods := []string{"apple", "papaya", "dragonfruit"}
```

Array:

```go
foods := [3]string{"apple", "papaya", "dragonfruit"}
```

For this course, when you think “Go list,” think **slice** first.

