## 4. Structs

A **struct** groups named fields together into one value. The Go spec describes composite literals for structs, and structs are the main way to model a record with named fields. ([Go][3])

```go
package main

import "fmt"

type Book struct {
    Title  string
    Author string
    Pages  int
}

func main() {
    book := Book{
        Title:  "Apple",
        Author: "Steve Jobs",
        Pages:  549,
    }

    fmt.Println(book)
    fmt.Println(book.Title)
}
```

### Real-world example: student

```go
package main

import "fmt"

type Student struct {
    Name      string
    Languages []string
    Active    bool
}

func main() {
    student := Student{
        Name:      "Mike",
        Languages: []string{"English", "Spanish", "French"},
        Active:    true,
    }

    fmt.Println(student)
    fmt.Println(student.Languages)
}
```

